text.tspan: When you contribute at least 5% of your pay, you’re taking full advantage of
thousands of dollars in matching funds from your agency or service over time.
Your agency or service will contribute up to 5%, on top of your salary or basic pay, to your
TSP account each paycheck. You will receive the full matching if you contribute at least 5%.
As a government civilian, you are entitled to the full match when you contribute 5% of your pay.
If you’ve opted-in to BRS, you are entitled to the full match when you contribute 5% of your pay.
It’s no longer all-or-nothing for service members
in BRS comes from the blending of two major sources of
retirement income: the existing annuity provision for those who retire after 20
or more years of service, plus the Thrift Savings Plan.
Includes matching contributions and assumes a 6% rate of return compounded monthly.
